script.name: !lib.packstation.dropped
script.description: Lib: Signal from when a station is built
script.sourceplaintext:
[THIS] ->set command: COMMAND_PACK_STATION $read.text = read text: page=6020 id=2081 [THIS] ->set command display override: text=$read.text $read.text = sprintf: pageid=6020 textid=2077, $a.station, null, null, null, null [THIS] ->set command extra display override: text=$read.text
$stored.stations = [THIS] -> get local variable: name='pack.station.stored' $stationWare = $a.station -> get ware type code of object skip if $stored.stations return null skip if $stored.stations[$stationWare] return null
$aStored = $stored.stations[$stationWare] skip if size of array $aStored return null
$tValues = $aStored[0] remove element from array $aStored at index 0
if not size of array $aStored remove key $stationWare from table $stored.stations if not size of table $stored.stations [THIS] ->remove secondary signal: signal=SIGNAL_BUILTSTATION, name='dropstation' [THIS] ->set local variable: name='pack.station.stored' value=null end end
* dock ships back to hq $aShips = $tValues['docked'] if $aShips $i = size of array $aShips while $i dec $i = $ship = $aShips[$i] @ START $ship -> call script !ship.cmd.movestation.std : object to land on=$a.station end end
* add the blueprints if $a.station -> is of class Headquarters $a.station ->set HQ queues: enabled=[TRUE]
$aBlueprins = $tValues['blueprints'] if $aBlueprins $current.hq = get player HQ do if $current.hq != $a.station $a.station ->set as player HQ
$i = size of array $aBlueprins while $i dec $i = $product = $aBlueprins[$i] add blueprints to player HQ: type=$product end
do if $current.hq != $a.station $current.hq ->set as player HQ end
* add the loadouts $tLoadouts = $tValues['loadouts'] if $tLoadouts $a.station ->remove all HQ loadouts $loadout.id = get next key: table=$tLoadouts key=null while $loadout.id $aLoadout = $tLoadouts[$loadout.id] $shiptype = $aLoadout[0] $name = $aLoadout[1] $aWares = $aLoadout[2] $aWeapons = $aLoadout[3] $new.id = $a.station ->create loadout: shiptype=$shiptype name=$name wares=$aWares $a.station ->set HQ loadout weapon order: id=$new.id weapons=$aWeapons $loadout.id = get next key: table=$tLoadouts key=$loadout.id end end
* add the production queue $aProducts = $tValues['productionqueue'] $aCounts = $tValues['productioncounts']
if $aProducts $aProducts = reverse array $aProducts $aCounts = reverse array $aCounts
$i = size of array $aProducts while $i dec $i = $product = $aProducts[$i] $count = $aCounts[$i] $a.station ->add to HQ production queue: $product Amount=$count end end
* move ships to reverse engineering queue $aShips = $tValues['reservequeue'] if $aShips $i = size of array $aShips while $i dec $i = $ship = $aShips[$i] @ START $ship -> call script !ship.cmd.reverseship.std : Headquarters=$a.station end end
* move ships to recycle queue $aShips = $tValues['recyclequeue'] if $aShips $i = size of array $aShips while $i dec $i = $ship = $aShips[$i] @ START $ship -> call script !ship.cmd.recycleship.std : Headquarters=$a.station end end
* move ships to repair queue $aShips = $tValues['repairqueue'] if $aShips $i = size of array $aShips while $i dec $i = $ship = $aShips[$i] @ START $ship -> call script !ship.cmd.repairship.std : Headquarters=$a.station end end
* add loadouts to hq else if $a.station -> is of class Factory if $tValues['upgrade'] $upgrade.level = $tValues['upgrade'] $a.station ->set upgrade level: $upgrade.level end $upgrade.progress = $tValues['upgradeprogress'] $a.station ->set upgrade progress: $upgrade.progress end
$a.station ->factory production task: on=[TRUE] end
if $a.station -> is of class Dock $aWares = $tValues['savedwares'] $i = size of array $aWares while $i dec $i = dec $i = $ware = $aWares[$i] $a.station ->add tradeable to dock: ware=$ware end end
$credits = $tValues['credits'] do if $credits $a.station ->transfer from player account: money=$credits, auto=[FALSE]
$name = $tValues['name'] $a.station ->set name to $name
$hull = $tValues['hull'] do if $hull $a.station ->set hull to $hull
if $a.station -> is of class Factory $value = $tValues['serial'] $a.station ->set serial name of station to $value end $value = $tValues['jumps.buy'] $a.station ->set max buy jumps: $value $value = $tValues['jumps.sell'] $a.station ->set max sell jumps: $value $value = $tValues['npc.trade'] $a.station ->set no npc docking allowed: $value $value = $tValues['no.warning'] $a.station ->set don't show warnings: $value $value = $tValues['mgr.repair.sy'] $a.station ->set station manager should repair ship with shipyards: on=$value $value = $tValues['mgr.repair.hq'] $a.station ->set station manager should repair ship with HQ: on=$value $value = $tValues['mgr.upgrade'] $a.station ->set station manager should upgrade ships: on=$value if $a.station -> is of class Headquarters $value = $tValues['mgr.loadout'] $a.station ->set station manager should stock for loadouts: on=$value end $value = $tValues['mgr.min.mony'] $a.station ->set station manager minimum money: $value $value = $tValues['mgr.min.upgrade'] $a.station ->set station manager minimum upgrade money: $value $value = $tValues['mgr.min.buy'] $a.station ->set station manager minimum buy ship money: $value $value = $tValues['mgr.min.repair'] $a.station ->set station manager minimum repair money: $value $value = $tValues['mgr.replace.sy'] $a.station ->set station manager should replace ships at shipyards: on=$value $value = $tValues['mgr.replace.hq'] $a.station ->set station manager should replace ships at HQ: on=$value $value = $tValues['favourite'] $a.station ->set favourite in property list: favourite=$value $value = $tValues['hidden'] $a.station ->set hidden in property list: hidden=$value $value = $tValues['prop.group'] do if $value $a.station ->set property custom group: id=$value $value = $tValues['transfer.values'] do if $value $a.station ->set local variable: name='transfer.values' value=$value $value = $tValues['mgr.wage'] do if $value $a.station ->set local variable: name='egosoft.stationmgr.wage' value=$value $value = $tValues['mgr.unpaid'] do if $value $a.station ->set local variable: name='egosoft.stationmgr.unpaid' value=$value $value = $tValues['mgr.supply'] if $value $key = get next key: table=$value key=null while $key $a.station ->add supply station: $key $key = get next key: table=$value key=$key end end $value = $tValues['mgr.restrict'] do if $value $a.station ->set local variable: name='stationmgr.restrict' value=$value
if $a.station -> is of class Dock $value = $tValues['type.product'] if $value $key = get next key: table=$value key=null while $key $a.station ->add tradeable to dock: ware=$key $a.station ->change ware to product: ware=$key $key = get next key: table=$value key=$key end end $value = $tValues['type.resource'] if $value $key = get next key: table=$value key=null while $key $a.station ->add tradeable to dock: ware=$key $a.station ->change ware to resource: ware=$key $key = get next key: table=$value key=$key end end $value = $tValues['type.storage'] if $value $key = get next key: table=$value key=null while $key $a.station ->add tradeable to dock: ware=$key $a.station ->change ware to storage: ware=$key $key = get next key: table=$value key=$key end end $value = $tValues['type.tradeable'] if $value $key = get next key: table=$value key=null while $key $a.station ->add tradeable to dock: ware=$key $a.station ->change ware to tradeable: ware=$key $key = get next key: table=$value key=$key end end end
$value = $tValues['minimum.storage'] if $value $key = get next key: table=$value key=null while $key $data = $value[$key] $a.station ->set minimum storage: ware=$key ,amount=$data $key = get next key: table=$value key=$key end end $value = $tValues['no.warning'] $a.station ->set don't show warnings: $value
$value = $tValues['agents'] if $value $key = get next key: table=$value key=null while $key $env = $key -> get environment $homebase = $key -> get homebase if ! $env OR $env == $homebase $key ->put into environment $a.station end $key ->set homebase to $a.station $key = get next key: table=$value key=$key end end
* add homebased ships $aShips = $tValues['ownedships'] $i = size of array $aShips while $i dec $i = $ship = $aShips[$i] $ship ->set homebase to $a.station end
$aWares = $tValues['warecost'] $ware = get next key: table=$aWares key=null while $ware $amt = $aWares[$ware] $a.station ->set price of ware $ware to $amt Cr $ware = get next key: table=$aWares key=$ware end
$value = $tValues['graph.data'] if $value $a.station ->start task [Task.Graph2] with script !lib.interrupt and prio 100: arg1=null arg2=null arg3=null arg4=null arg5=null @ = wait 100 ms $a.station ->set local variable: name='graph.data' value=$value $a.station ->start task [Task.Graph2] with script graph.data.collector.station and prio 50: arg1=null arg2=null arg3=null arg4=null arg5=null end
* dock at HQ and add the wares if $a.dowares $aWares = $tValues['savedwares'] if size of array $aWares [THIS] ->set destination to $a.station [THIS] ->set command: COMMAND_DOCKAT
if $a.station -> is docking possible of [THIS] while [DOCKEDAT] != $a.station @ = wait 1000 ms @ = [THIS] -> call script !move.movetostation : station=$a.station end
$value = $tValues['marines'] if $value $i = size of array $value while $i dec $i = $marine = $value[$i] = [THIS] ->unload marine: $marine end end
$i = size of array $aWares while $i dec $i = $amt = $aWares[$i] dec $i = $ware = $aWares[$i] = [THIS] -> unload $amt units of $ware end
else $ship.size = [THIS] -> get size of object $station.size = $a.station -> get size of object $range = $ship.size + $station.size + 2500 @ = [THIS] -> call script !move.movetoobject.samesector : Target=$a.station Range=$range $tSendWares = table alloc $i = size of array $aWares while $i dec $i = $amt = $aWares[$i] dec $i = $ware = $aWares[$i] $amt = - $amt $tSendWares[$ware] = $amt end @ = [THIS] -> call script !ship.cmd.freighttransfer.std : Target Ship=$a.station Wares table=$tSendWares Unload?=[TRUE] end end end
unlock achievement: id='ACH_MOVE_STATION'
* hired TL, move back home first if [TRUEOWNER] != Player @ = [THIS] -> call script !move.undock :
$home.sector = [THIS] ->is in home sector if [HOMEBASE] -> exists @ = [THIS] -> call script !ship.cmd.returnhome.std : else if $home.sector -> exists @ = [THIS] -> call script !move.movetosector : sector=$home.sector end
if [THIS] -> get job id [THIS] ->start job end end
return null
